## CSS Classes Added Automatically

When you call `initBrowserCompatibility()`, these classes are automatically added to the `<body>` element:

### Browser Classes
- `browser-chrome`
- `browser-firefox`
- `browser-safari`
- `browser-edge`
- `browser-version-120` (example)

### Device Classes
- `is-mobile`
- `is-ios`
- `is-android`

### Feature Support Classes
- `supports-backdrop-filter`
- `supports-css-grid`
- `supports-web-socket`
- `no-backdrop-filter` (if not supported)
- etc.

### Usage in CSS

```css
/* Target specific browsers */
.browser-safari .glass-card {
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
}

/* Target mobile devices */
.is-mobile .card {
  padding: 12px;
}

/* Provide fallbacks for unsupported features */
.no-backdrop-filter .glass-card {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
}
```

